## Pending Fixes

### Fix: _auto_launch_daemon should use full powershell path as fallback
- When appendWindowsPath=false in /etc/wsl.conf, powershell.exe is not on PATH
- _auto_launch_daemon() fails silently because it uses bare powershell.exe
- Fix: add _find_powershell() that tries shutil.which first, then full path /mnt/c/Windows/System32/WindowsPowerShell/v1.0/powershell.exe
- File: computer_use/platform/wsl2.py, line ~1012

## Pending Bugs

### Bug 1: Step shows "done" when agent internally failed
- Executor emits "Step N complete" when subprocess exits 0, even if agent wrote "FAILED" in output
- Root cause: executor has no structured way to know if a step succeeded
- Fix: JSON step output (being implemented now)

### Bug 2: Computer use enabled but agent says tools not available
- CLI/API shows computer_use: enabled (MCP configs written)
- But running Claude Code session doesn't reload MCP configs
- Agent logs "Computer use tools not available"
- Fix: after enabling computer use, tell user to restart Claude Code
- Also: check if MCP server is actually reachable before reporting "enabled"

### Bug 3: Computer use enable message should say restart needed
- "forge computer-use enable" says "enabled" but doesn't mention restart
- Should say: "Computer use enabled. Restart any running agents for changes to take effect."
